<h1 >Current Research Interests (2019)</h1>
 </center> </div>
<hr>
<br><br>
<h3>
<p><u> Effective Field Theories of Topological States of Matter 
</u></p>

<ul>
<li>Conformal field theories describing edge excitations in the quantum
Hall effect 
</li> <br>
<li> Experimental signatures of fractional statistics in 2D</li><br>
<li> Stability of topological phases phases of matter in 2D and 3D </li><br>
<li> Surface excitations in 3D systems </li><br>
<li> Duality relations among field theories in (2+1) dimensions </li><br>
</ul>

<br><br>

<p><u>Conformal invariance in two dimensions and higher dimensions</u></p>

<ul>
<li> Numerical conformal bootstrap between two and four dimension </li> <br>
<li> Irreversibility of the renormalization-group flow and C-theorem in more than two dimensions  </li><br>
</ul>
<br><br>

<u><p>History of physics</u></p>

<ul>
<li> In 2012, together with F. Colomo, E. Castellani (Florence) and 
P. Di Vecchia (Stockholm) we edited a collective book on the early history 
of string theory </li> <br>
<li> We organize some afternoons with physics an philosophy
colloquia (see homepage) </li><br>
</ul>
